  "local_port": 36822,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some shows similar to Leverage?",
  "response": "If you enjoyed *Leverage*, which revolves around a team of skilled con artists and thieves who use their talents to take down corrupt individuals and corporations, you might also like the following shows:\n\n1. **Hustle** (2004-2012)  \n   A British series about a group of con artists who pull off elaborate scams to swindle greedy and dishonest individuals. It has a similar tone to *Leverage* with its witty dialogue and clever heists.\n\n2. **White Collar** (2009-2014)  \n   This series follows a brilliant con artist who partners with an FBI agent to solve white-collar crimes. It combines crime-solving with cons and has a charming, playful vibe.\n\n3. **Burn Notice** (2007-2013)  \n   A former spy, blacklisted and stranded in Miami, uses his skills to help people while trying to uncover the truth behind his burn notice. It features a mix of action, humor, and teamwork.\n\n4. **The Mentalist** (2008-2015)  \n   A former psychic medium uses his keen observational skills to solve crimes as a consultant for the California Bureau of Investigation. It has a similar cleverness and focus on outsmarting opponents.\n\n5. **Person of Interest** (2011-2016)  \n   A mysterious billionaire and a former CIA operative use a surveillance AI to prevent violent crimes before they happen. It features a mix of action, intrigue, and a team dynamic.\n\n6. **Ocean's Eleven** (2001 Movie and its sequels)  \n   While not a TV show, this heist film (and its sequels) features a similar theme of a team of specialists pulling off elaborate cons and heists with style and humor.\n\n7. **Sneaky Pete** (2015-2019)  \n   A con artist assumes the identity of his former cellmate to escape a dangerous criminal, only to get entangled in a new con with his \"family.\" It\u2019s packed with twists and clever schemes.\n\n8. **The Blacklist** (2013-2023)  \n   A former criminal turned FBI informant helps the agency track down other dangerous criminals. It has a mix of cons, crime-solving, and intriguing character dynamics.\n\n9. **Imposters** (2017-2018)  \n   A con artist who marries and then swindles her victims is pursued by her exes in this darkly comedic series. It has a similar mix of cons and unexpected twists.\n\n10. **Limitless** (2015-2016)  \n    Based on the movie of the same name, a man uses a drug that enhances his abilities to help the FBI solve crimes. It\u2019s quirky, clever, and fast-paced.\n\nThese shows share themes of teamwork, cleverness, and outsmarting the bad guys, often with a sense of humor and style.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
